<Author>norinice
<Content>Lovely! This is a really nice place to stay. Well run, clean, beautifully maintained grounds. They must spend a fortune in landscaping alone because the gardens and greenery are superb!The pools are fabulous. Staying here allows you use of the facilities at the JW Marriott which are amazing. A shuttle transports guests between the two hotels all day.There is a large, entertaining mall just down the road with everything you could imagine. The shuttle also transports you there if you like. I had a rental car and prefer to drive myself.The shuttles are nice though and the staff all around treats you like royalty. Very sophisticated.If you have kids this is the place for you for sure. They will spend the whole day in the many, many pools and be happy.My only possible complaints would be (and this isn't the fault of the hotel per se) the complete lack of any interesting food choices in the area. I can only take but so many chain restaurants. Also, there is a shortage of things to do in the evening. The JW has a lounge singer in the cocktail bar which is nice. But there's really nothing going on at night. Drinks are attractive and well made, but pricey.I can't rave enough about the flora and fauna on the grounds. Quail, rabbits, duck, lizards, cacti. I have tons of pictures I'll definately post. This place is gorgeous! The king size bed has quality cotton sheets and is comfy. The rooms are incredibly clean. Get a one or two bedroom for more than one person because they come with a full size kitchen and living area. The studios are tight. Bring your family here. Relax, and enjoy yourself. I'll be back for sure! Thumbs up! 
