<Content>Studios very small We stayed Nov 2-Nov 9 2008. Booked through II and got a studio unit as that was all that was available. The studio is very, very small and would not recommend more than 2 in the unit. The small bar area is the designated area for the coffee maker and toaster, but it was a juggling act every morning making breakfast. There is a bar size fridge and microwave. They supply 2 packs of coffee but no filters which we found rather odd. The sink is too small to really do dishes, so we purchased disposables - great for us bad for the environment. The lock-off is not at all sound proof - you can hear everything - I mean everything! The resort is beautifual and staff awesome. The staff mapquested everything we asked. Would stay again but only in a 1 bedroom unit. 
