<Content>glad we bought here We had our first arizona holiday last year when we enjoyed two stays at the desert ridge hotel (two weeks and then a short break of four days). During this time we viewed the timeshare villas at canyon villas and purchased a two bed two week package.We used the accommodation this summer for the first time. We totally loved the experience! The villas are roomy and very well equipped. My son and his girl friend had the lock off portion of the villa and my husband and two other children shared the one bed portion. We had ample space to spread out - with three rooms, two balconies, two bathrooms and three televisions. The kitchen was very well appointed and I enjoyed cooking in the open-plan living/dining room. Cooking for ourselves on the barbecues or in the villa gave us the opportunity to try the excellent meat and fish available at Albertsons (in the desert ridge mall).The villas are low rise (three floors) so the views over the deserts are not as good as from the higher floors in the hotel next door. We had a top floor villa in the 2800 block. We heard nothing from neighbours - although I was alerted to the possibility in an earlier post. We really heard nothing from anyone - in two weeks!!! I understand that there are blocks that are better suited to people with young children - additional small pools and squirting fountains - perhaps that is why the part of the complex we stayed in was so quiet.The only problem that we encountered during our stay was when we were checking in - the room was not ready until nearly five o'clock - just our luck to check in on a Saturday - but the day before we checked in and during the time I was waiting for our room many people were able to access our room - perhaps it was because of the time it takes to clean a two bed villa as opposed to a one bed or studio apartment. Anyway, we were given a $20 credit to have a drink in the bar whilst the room was finished off. Matt was pleasant - as has previously been stated. The pool areas were rarely crowded and I must admit we used them most days and did not venture to the desert ridge hotel more than once (I had previously stayed there with my son for two weeks waiting for the rest of my family to join us).My boys prefered the layout of the villas pools and there was always the opportunity for us to get six sunbeds together.We tried the hot hot hot tubs on a couple of occasions - quite pleasant in the relative cool of evening - but scorchio during the day - who wants a hot bath when the temperature is 105 degrees?We will definitely be returning to the canyon villas next summer and are pleased that we made the decision to become owners here - although we do recognise that in July and August the published rates for the villas are exceptional value. 
